    <note>Zheng(1) Qingzhi [10363] Liu Kezhuang, WJ, 170.1a ff. His original mingzi was Xie, which suggests that it may have been changed because of kinship ties with Yuan(1) Xie [10289]. He cooperated with Shi(5) Miyuan [3727] in setting the policy that placed Zhao(1) Lizhong [9014] on the throne. In Yuan(1) Jue's [10286] funerary inscription, Qingzhi instead of Chongzhi [10362] is designated as Jue's wife's great grandfather. CBD, 5, 3704-6.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:1228:  Apt. Jianshu Shumiyuan shi (State Council).1230:  Transferred to Canzhi zhengshi.1233:  Replaced Shi Miyuan as You chengxiang (Chief minister) when Miyuan retired and died.1235:  Trasferred to Zuo chengxiang (Chief minister)1236:  Dismiised to a Taoist temple sinecure.1244:  Apt. You chengxiang concurrently Taifu and Shumi yuan shi.1249:  (run mo.) Transferred to Zuo chengxiang and made Taishi.1251:  Died in office.</note>
